    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>Jany 26/59</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear &amp; Respected Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I had the<lb/> honor of addressing you a few lines<lb/> on
                        <date>21<hi rend="sup">st</hi> November</date> last, stating that<lb/> I had
                written <persName>Hon. Thos. Co. Florence</persName><lb/> enclosing your letter to
                him on <date>13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Octo.</date><lb/> (as I called on him several
                times without<lb/> succeeding in seeing him) and that<lb/> I had not then (&amp;
                have not yet) heard<lb/> from in reply, and would<lb/> not then have troubled you
                about<lb/> it but that I was so desirous<lb/> (&amp; am still) of obtaining the
                appointment<lb/> of commissioner for <placeName>Pennsylvania</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Father would like you to<lb/> send him his bill of indebtedness</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>for the Occident.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">By the way, did <persName>L. Powers</persName><lb/> pay you for the
                Prayer Book<lb/> he got of you: if not, if you<lb/> will send me the Bill, I
                will<lb/> endeavor to collect it for you here,<lb/> from <persName>L. Y.
                    Martin</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My Parents desire to be<lb/> kindly remembered.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I Remain Dr. Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Yours Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">J. Solis Ritterband</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>224 Bowery</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
